To compare the four cultures on the cultural dimensions, we again applied MANOVAs on the raw scores and MACS analyses to examine latent mean differences. We found no significant effects involving gender, so we report results for a MANOVA with culture as the sole independent variable. The main effect for culture was statistically significant (Wilks’ Lambda = .63), F(12, 2,313) = 36.91, p < .01. Follow-up ANOVAs revealed significant cultural differences for each of the cultural dimensions and the effect sizes (
η p 2
) were all large (Cohen, 1988). Table 2 shows the results.
